4: Fine... But don't say I didn't warn you!
7:
We did a thorough search of the
area but didn't observe anything
amiss.
10:
I see... Thank you. I'm sorry to call
upon you for guard duty of all things.
15:
Don't be. We're happy to help, but...
are you okay? You're not looking so
good.
19:
I haven't seen you take a break even
once the entire time we've been
here. I think it's time you got some
rest.
30:
Sarliha! You've done enough work
for today. Okay?
40:
Huh? Sarliha?! I thought you were
supposed to be resting.
44:
I am. I'm taking the day off, so I
thought I might spend the time here,
if you don't mind.
48:
I mean, you're always welcome in
Starview, but that encyclopedia sure
doesn't look like it's for leisure.
52:
Oh, yes, well... If I can't be up and
about, I thought I'd at least spend
my break studying.
57:
...Look, I heard what you're working
for. But I don't get why you're
pushing yourself this hard.
61:
You're... worried about me? I got the
impression that you—
65:
Don't change the subject. You've got
royal blood, don't you?
66: So why? Why are YOU fighting?
71:
As a child, I had a dear friend... who
happened to be an orphan.
73:
I didn't fully understand why, but the
adults were desperate to keep me
away from her.
75:
We'd sneak out to play anyway, but
then one day, a snake bit her, and...
the venom...
83:
She SHOULD have been, though! If
they'd just administered an
antidote, she wouldn't have—she...
86:
I... finally saw how little her life had
been valued by our society—and all
because of the circumstances she
was born into.
90:
It isn't right! I will NEVER forget that
day.
97:
Sarliha. I've SEEN someone try to fix
it. And he was making a hell of a lot
more progress than you.
99:
But you know how that ended for
him? ...He was murdered.
102:
And the way you're going, it's only a
matter of time until you get yourself
killed too.
105:
I recognize that risk. But it's all the
more reason to study.
107:
Perhaps I'll find a way to protect
everyone. Somehow, some way...
113:
Maybe not. But I would rather do
SOMETHING than nothing.
115:
I want to make a difference, no
matter how small.
118:
And I know... that's what Rolan would
have wanted too.
126:
I'm sorry, Nimbus... I wish I could
have prevented it.
132:
Nothing I say's gonna change your
mind, so forget I said anything.
137:
Ah! Nimbus, wait! I realize this is
insensitive of me to ask, but...
139:
Would you mind telling me about
him?
143:
You're completely right. I've been too
reckless for too little results.
145:
So I'd like to learn more. About
Rolan's goals, his methods...
148:
His "methods" sure as hell didn't pan
out for HIM.
151:
But you yourself said he made more
progress than me. Right?
161:
...FINE. But don't get your hopes up. I
never knew much about politics.
166:
That's all right, anything helps. He's
the best example I have!
177: Oh, Nimbus, thank you so much!
185: I'll go fetch you some drinks.
188:
And Sarliha? After this, take the rest
of the day off for REAL, okay?
191:
Yeah, let's make that my condition.
I'm not talkin' unless you chill.
196:
Oooh, all right. I'll do my best! T-to
relax, I mean!
